&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a positive, reliable and highly motivated individual to join our forward looking practice. The Patient Co-Ordinator will be responsible for the day-to-day delivery of the front of house service within the practice. They will work as part of our dynamic team to help provide a streamline and effective service for our patients by answering calls, emails and face to face enquiries and finding the best possible solution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience working in NHS administration or in any receptionist type role is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This excellent opportunity is for around 20 hours per week and is a permanent position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, please contact the practice manager, Louise Bridle via email at louise.bridle@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: Friday 19/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Here are committed to equality and valuing diversity.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
